TITLE.P: Procurement of license management (Licensing Solution Provider) and Microsoft licenses.

SHORT_DESCR.P: The objective of the procurement is to establish a framework agreement with an LSP (Licensing Solution Provider) to establish and manage all standard products and cloud service from Microsoft and take responsibility for deliveries from Microsoft.

The Contracting Authority currently has an EA/SCE direct agreement with Microsoft, and also CSP and MPSA agreements with a service provider for the purchase of software, maintenance and license consultancy services for products from Microsoft. The EA/SCE direct agreement and the MPSA agreement expire 31.10.2018, and a new agreement must be established with Microsoft before the expiry of the direct agreement.

The framework shall secure good flexibility for the Contracting Authority in order to cover new and changed need for products and services from Microsoft, and the Contracting Authority anticipates increased use of new technology and services from implementation and planning of large restructuring.

The framework agreement shall cover the needs of the various products identified in the Tender Documentation Annex 1 for the Norwegian Labour and Welfare Administration. The framework agreement shall also cover the Contracting Authority’s need for new technology and gradual transition to could services during the agreement period.

The procurement shall continue licenses, maintain services and cloud services for the Microsoft products that the contracting authority currently has. Overview of the products is documented in the Tender Documentation Annex 1.
The service provider shall fill the role of LSP for Microsoft products, and this shall include:
— Administration/management of the Contracting Authority’s agreements and licenses. The Contracting Authority currently has the following agreements EA/SCE, Select, MPSA and CSP,
— Secure optimal licensing and prices that are correct in the market,
— Take total responsibility for Microsoft’s deliveries to the Contracting Authority.
It shall be possible to procure consultancy services. Access to competence, resources and availability, including:
— Support services such as adoption of software,

— Consultancy services and consulting, i.a. to ensure successful introduction of cloud services and to assist the Contracting authority in planning prioritised order for successful introduction of new technology,

RENEWAL_DESCR.P: Option for an extension for 12 months. The contract shall have a duration of 3 years from signing. The Contracting Authority (the Customer) has the option to extend the contract for a further 1 year.

CRITERIA_CANDIDATE.P: The selection of the tenderer will be based on the degree of compliance with the qualification requirements in the qualification documentation, point 2.4:

OPTIONS_DESCR.P: Option for an extension for 12 months. The contract shall have a duration of 3 years from signing. The contracting authority (the Customer) has the option to extend the contract for a further 1 year.

SUITABILITY.P: Qualification Requirements: The tenderer is required to be a legally established company.
— Norwegian tenderers: Company registration certificate from the Brønnøysund Register Centre.
— Foreign tenderers: Certificate for registration in the company register as prescribed in the legislation of the country in which the tenderer is established.
Qualification Requirement: Norwegian tenderers shall have their tax and VAT payments in order.
Norwegian tenderers: A Tax and VAT certificate from the tax authorities, not older than 6 months calculated from the deadline for requests to participate in the tender contest.

ECONOMIC_FINANCIAL_INFO.P: Qualification requirement: The supplier is required to have good financial solidity.
The Contracting Authority will obtain credit ratings carried out by Experian; see www.Experian.no.
If the tenderer feels that the credit rating will not provide an accurate picture, please send supplementary information together with the qualification application.

TECHNICAL_PROFESSIONAL_INFO.P: Qualification Requirement: Very good implementation ability is required.
Documentation Requirement: Description of the tenderer's capacity that includes.
— A description that gives a comprehensive overview of the units at the Tenderer that are relevant for the scope in the framework agreement,
— Number of relevant resources in accordance with the content and scope of the procurement within:
—— Technical consulting/product specialist for Microsoft technology.
—— Audits and negotiations on Microsoft products.
—— Introduction projects for cloud services and new technology.
The template in annex 2 to the qualification documentation shall be used for the other points. The personnel proposed to the assignment shall not be specified, and CVs not submitted.
Regarding the above named description, the Tenderer must take into account the contents of point 1.3 and 1.4 in the qualification documentation.
Qualification Requirement: Relevant experience from similar deliveries is required.
Documentation requirement:
Description shall include up to three of the tenderer’s primary, relevant deliveries during the last three years cf. Point 1.3 and 1.4 in the qualification documentation.
Description on each delivery shall include.
— recipient/contracting authority,
— date and duration,
— discipline,
— Value (if the value cannot be specified due to confidentiality requirements, the Tenderer is asked to specify the number of man-labour years for the Tenderer's input),
— The tenderer's role/area of responsibility,
— Description of the delivery including system/technology that was used.
The template in annex 3 of the qualification documentation shall be used for this point.
Name and contact details for the reference client’s contact person who can confirm this information must be provided on request.
Qualification requirements: Good and well functioning methods for quality assurance are required.
Documentation requirement:

— A brief description of the service provider's general methods and processes that are relevant in ensuring the quality of the service. There should be no sales text, product descriptions or descriptions of experience.
— An account of the company’s quality assurance system and any certificates issued by independent bodies.
